      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HILLTOP CRUNCH (4) started a hot favourite when making his debut here on Monday but manners let him down. Had shown ability at the trials prior and should have learned from the raceday experience so prepared to give him another chance. IDEAL MIKI (1) did a good job to come from this barrier and finish 2.5 metres from the winner in second on debut at this circuit and distance. Has trialled well since and is likely to get the favours from this draw. MYA QUICK (3) is at the track for the first time. By top sire Art Major and hails from the Tyson Linke stable. Has the benefit of a good draw and was not far away in a recent trial. Should be ready to run a big race. FARROH GODDESS (2) broke on debut but draws well so could be worth another chance.",
